snippet.textDisplay: Guys, Turbo can cause a lot of trouble, what boost are you runing? I would think, when you introduce turbo, you would want to machine your cylinders in order to reduce compression, otherwise you will end up with premature ignition and knock, which can in turn destroy the cylinder and or rods. If you rebuild the engine, I would certainly recommend doing the math and make sure there is no knock. Good luck, I love the project 👍🏻👍🏻

I would think, when you introduce turbo, you would want to machine your cylinders in order to reduce compression, otherwise you will end up with premature ignition and knock, which can in turn destroy the cylinder and or rods.
